01:18:44,358 --> 01:18:45,373
War?

968
01:18:46,278 --> 01:18:49,410
You're with us.
The hell I am.

969
01:18:54,471 --> 01:18:56,380
All right, I'm with you.

970
01:18:57,479 --> 01:19:00,348
So just lie low.
Sleep some more.

971
01:19:02,246 --> 01:19:04,254
Laura, she said
you should sleep.

972
01:19:15,175 --> 01:19:17,347
(MAN TALKING ON TV)

973
01:19:22,662 --> 01:19:24,670
BRAIN: Brendan?
Yeah.

974
01:19:24,743 --> 01:19:26,815
Are you... What?
Man, have you heard
about Dode?

975
01:19:26,887 --> 01:19:27,869
I was there.
You...

976
01:19:27,943 --> 01:19:29,219
Where were you yesterday?
I called.

977
01:19:29,287 --> 01:19:32,004
Kasprzyk took my phone,
turned it off.
I just now got it back.

978
01:19:32,071 --> 01:19:33,664
All right, listen.
Are you okay?

979
01:19:33,735 --> 01:19:35,011
Just listen.

980
01:19:35,079 --> 01:19:37,534
Is my name in the papers
with the story?
No.

981
01:19:37,607 --> 01:19:39,168
All right.
Is it just Dode's name
in the papers?

982
01:19:39,239 --> 01:19:40,253
Yeah. What do you mean?

983
01:19:40,327 --> 01:19:43,294
Listen, I'm gonna be
calling you tonight,
probably late.

984
01:19:43,367 --> 01:19:46,117
So sleep with your phone on.
Could you get a car
if you needed to?

985
01:19:46,183 --> 01:19:50,274
If it's late enough
I could take my mom's.
Be ready then. I'll call.

986
01:19:53,063 --> 01:19:54,973
Brendan,
did you hear about Dode?

987
01:19:55,046 --> 01:19:57,381
You scheming tramp.
You set that poor kid up.

988
01:19:57,447 --> 01:20:01,091
You held Dode like a card
till you could play him.
For money!

989
01:20:02,278 --> 01:20:03,740
I don't know what
you're talking about.

990
01:20:03,815 --> 01:20:06,270
You'd bury me at
the same time, but it was
mostly for the money.

991
01:20:06,343 --> 01:20:08,579
You got Dode thinking
Em had his kid,
thinking I did it,

992
01:20:08,647 --> 01:20:10,556
and that was enough for him,
but he stuck to the money,

993
01:20:10,631 --> 01:20:11,907
'cause you had
your claws in him!

994
01:20:11,974 --> 01:20:15,171
'Cause he couldn't come away
from the deal without it
and make you happy!

995
01:20:15,239 --> 01:20:18,239
Brendan, I think you just need
to just sit down for a second.

996
01:20:18,342 --> 01:20:20,415
I think you're just
a mess right now.

997
01:20:20,487 --> 01:20:24,480
Can you please, sweetheart,
could you go run and get
my shoes from my locker?

998
01:20:32,998 --> 01:20:35,781
Still wish you knew
what you wanted to know?

999
01:20:39,143 --> 01:20:41,598
You know, if it's any
consolation,
it probably wasrt Dode's kid.

1000
01:20:41,671 --> 01:20:44,868
It might have been Tug's kid.
Frankly,
I wouldn't bet a horse.

1001
01:20:44,935 --> 01:20:48,732
It was kind of a crowded field
there at the end,
if you know what I mean.

1002
01:21:02,183 --> 01:21:03,328
Meanie.

1003
01:21:05,830 --> 01:21:07,586
(KARA SCREAMING)

1004
01:21:07,654 --> 01:21:08,603
(THUDDING)

1005
01:21:09,062 --> 01:21:11,484
KARA: What are you doing?
Showing your ace.

1006
01:21:12,231 --> 01:21:13,376
PIN: Far enough.

1007
01:21:15,143 --> 01:21:17,150
Everyone's paying
social calls.

1008
01:21:17,831 --> 01:21:19,554
So what are the stats?

1009
01:21:20,007 --> 01:21:22,560
The stats are war.
Tug got hot. He panicked.

1010
01:21:22,631 --> 01:21:24,289
Tug's been after my digs
from the get-go.

1011
01:21:24,359 --> 01:21:26,847
No, he's been anxious,
'cause he thought if you
found out he killed Emily,

1012
01:21:26,919 --> 01:21:27,966
you'd turn him over.

1013
01:21:28,039 --> 01:21:29,664
He was right.
Yeah, well.

1014
01:21:30,342 --> 01:21:34,052
I told him to get this
straight, no roughing.
I wasrt even there.

1015
01:21:34,119 --> 01:21:36,541
All right, so he's a hothead.
So you don't want him
on your side.

1016
01:21:36,614 --> 01:21:38,916
At least let's have a pow-wow
before we start
digging trenches.

1017
01:21:38,982 --> 01:21:41,371
Maybe we can all walk away
amiable enemies.

1018
01:21:43,334 --> 01:21:44,861
Yeah, all right.

1019
01:21:45,063 --> 01:21:46,753
4:00.
Tomorrow?

1020
01:21:46,822 --> 01:21:49,670
Tonight.
Let's clear it all
before it boils up again.

1021
01:21:50,887 --> 01:21:51,999
Wait!

1022
01:21:53,575 --> 01:21:55,266
I'll drive you back.

1023
01:21:59,271 --> 01:22:00,383
So here's the sit.

1024
01:22:00,454 --> 01:22:02,047
You and The Pin
are gonna pow-wow, tonight.

1025
01:22:02,118 --> 01:22:03,427
4:00, his place.

1026
01:22:03,494 --> 01:22:05,349
Bring all the muscle you want,
you won't need it.

1027
01:22:05,414 --> 01:22:06,363
He wants to talk straight,

1028
01:22:06,439 --> 01:22:08,381
and you're gonna work with him
for whatever he needs.

1029
01:22:08,455 --> 01:22:10,309
'Cause you don't want war.
The hell I don't.

1030
01:22:10,375 --> 01:22:13,189
The Pin's sitting on
the brick profits.
Hitting him now would be post.

1031
01:22:13,255 --> 01:22:15,262
Make peace,
wait for your chance.

1032
01:22:15,655 --> 01:22:17,565
He's right, Tug.
Smooth it out.

1033
01:22:17,638 --> 01:22:18,882
(COUGHING)

1034
01:22:19,239 --> 01:22:21,508
Besides, he's got you
on the Dode thing.

1035
01:22:21,574 --> 01:22:24,608
War will mean you versus him
and every bull in the burgh.

1036
01:22:25,735 --> 01:22:27,295
Yeah, we'll talk.

1037
01:22:28,135 --> 01:22:29,542
You going?
Yeah.

1038
01:22:46,471 --> 01:22:47,616
(DOOR OPENING)

1039
01:22:49,255 --> 01:22:50,433
(SIGHING)

1040
01:22:50,503 --> 01:22:51,713
Go away.

1041
01:23:11,046 --> 01:23:12,737
I'm sorry, Brendan.

1042
01:23:27,718 --> 01:23:29,125
I'm so sorry.

1043
01:24:19,398 --> 01:24:20,958
Don't go tonight.

1044
01:24:23,238 --> 01:24:25,824
I gotta make sure
everything plays out smooth.

1045
01:24:26,470 --> 01:24:29,220
It'll play out
however it plays,
without you there.

1046
01:24:29,287 --> 01:24:31,075
I gotta make sure.

1047
01:24:31,367 --> 01:24:32,447
Why?

1048
01:24:32,550 --> 01:24:34,852
'Cause if there's war,
I'm in it, too.

1049
01:24:41,478 --> 01:24:43,005
I'm just scared.

1050
01:24:44,166 --> 01:24:45,988
If things go bad tonight...

1051
01:24:47,398 --> 01:24:48,925
Just be careful.

1052
01:25:22,726 --> 01:25:24,581
Your folks left a car here?
Yeah.

1053
01:25:24,646 --> 01:25:26,337
Take it and Laura's.
I'll go first in yours.

1054
01:25:26,406 --> 01:25:27,421
The hell you'll take mine.

1055
01:25:27,495 --> 01:25:28,989
The scenic route.
Draw off any tailers.

1056
01:25:29,063 --> 01:25:31,714
They'll think it's you,
might even radio back
you're alone.

1057
01:25:31,783 --> 01:25:33,092
Mr. Smarts.

1058
01:25:34,534 --> 01:25:36,094
You got a cigarette?

1059
01:25:36,647 --> 01:25:39,200
I don't smoke.
I've seen you smoke.

1060
01:25:39,654 --> 01:25:41,596
I don't smoke cigarettes.

1061
01:25:42,790 --> 01:25:44,700
Give me 15 minutes, then go.

1062
01:25:46,022 --> 01:25:47,135
BRENDAN: Write this down.

1063
01:25:47,207 --> 01:25:49,345
I'm gonna be out of The Pin's
by 4:15.

1064
01:25:49,415 --> 01:25:52,731
So at exactly 4:15,
you put an anonymous call
into the bulls.

1065
01:25:53,030 --> 01:25:56,227
You tell them there are drugs
in the trunk
of the black Mustang

1066
01:25:56,295 --> 01:25:57,669
outside The Pin's house.

1067
01:25:57,734 --> 01:25:59,938
Can you get the car?
BRAIN: Yeah.

1068
01:26:00,006 --> 01:26:03,487
All right,
after you call the cops,
go to Tug's house. 12 Elm.

1069
01:26:03,558 --> 01:26:06,079
Park outside and wait.
Laura's inside.

1070
01:26:06,151 --> 01:26:10,373
She hasn't got a car, but if
she blows on foot or gets
a pick, tail her. All right?

1071
01:26:11,815 --> 01:26:13,603
All right?
Okay.

1072
01:26:15,910 --> 01:26:17,917
I'll call you
when it gets light.

1073
01:26:22,022 --> 01:26:23,298
Thanks, Brain.

1074
01:26:52,135 --> 01:26:53,345
(CAR APPROACHING)

1075
01:27:16,550 --> 01:27:17,630
Talk.

1076
01:27:20,423 --> 01:27:24,132
I want full assurance that
any heat from Emily and Dode
is on just you.

1077
01:27:25,479 --> 01:27:28,196
I don't even want my name
pulled into the shindig.

1078
01:27:29,190 --> 01:27:31,612
Second, you owe me six C's.

1079
01:27:32,262 --> 01:27:33,440
No rush.

1080
01:27:34,215 --> 01:27:37,149
But I want your shake
that they'll be home
in not too much time.

1081
01:27:37,222 --> 01:27:39,426
That's square.
You did them, after all.

1082
01:27:39,494 --> 01:27:41,828
Lay low, it'll blow over.
Stick on this,

1083
01:27:41,895 --> 01:27:45,408
one of you will dish it
to bury the other.
You'll both get the rap.

1084
01:27:45,479 --> 01:27:47,518
As for the six,
did you borrow it?

1085
01:27:48,070 --> 01:27:49,117
Yeah.

1086
01:27:49,190 --> 01:27:51,873
Then you owe it.
Shouldrt need
a shake on that.

1087
01:27:52,455 --> 01:27:55,324
All right to both.
Good. Let's seal it up
and blow for keeps.

1088
01:27:55,398 --> 01:27:56,510
Third thing,

1089
01:27:57,190 --> 01:27:58,684
the last brick...

1090
01:27:59,046 --> 01:28:00,355
It's yours.

1091
01:28:01,095 --> 01:28:02,818
That's not the point.

1092
01:28:03,142 --> 01:28:05,149
I'm gonna start selling it.

1093
01:28:05,606 --> 01:28:07,362
How do I know it's not bad?

1094
01:28:07,654 --> 01:28:10,142
Why would it be?
Why was the last one?

1095
01:28:11,559 --> 01:28:13,533
Because someone got greedy.

1096
01:28:14,630 --> 01:28:18,754
Tug here's had the means to
swipe half of it and
cut it bad for a long time.

1097
01:28:19,142 --> 01:28:21,989
Now we're splits,
the loss of my trust
is retroactive.

1098
01:28:22,054 --> 01:28:25,022
Did you, Tug?
No.

1099
01:28:25,095 --> 01:28:27,942
All right,
let's shake and blow.
Not good enough.

1100
01:28:28,550 --> 01:28:30,241
What would be good enough?

1101
01:28:31,206 --> 01:28:34,523
I want to see him dose it,
just to prove it.

1102
01:28:35,750 --> 01:28:36,699
Then we're square.

1103
01:28:36,775 --> 01:28:40,703
Hell for that.
I didn't touch your junk!
That's all!

1104
01:28:40,774 --> 01:28:42,203
I wanna see it.
To hell!

1105
01:28:42,279 --> 01:28:44,734
Your not wanting to dose,
it's proving something to me
right here.

1106
01:28:44,807 --> 01:28:46,214
Oh, it better be.

1107
01:28:46,278 --> 01:28:48,733
It's telling
that I ain't under your thumb
no more!

1108
01:28:48,806 --> 01:28:51,970
That I ain't playing lapdog
to no gothed-up cripple!

1109
01:28:55,463 --> 01:28:56,837
I'll dose it.

1110
01:28:57,254 --> 01:28:58,203
What?

1111
01:28:58,278 --> 01:29:00,188
If that'll shut you
two apes up,
I'll take the dose.

1112
01:29:00,263 --> 01:29:02,564
If I don't die,
we're all right as rain.

1113
01:29:03,942 --> 01:29:05,022
Deal?

1114
01:29:06,694 --> 01:29:07,806
Fine.

1115
01:29:09,830 --> 01:29:11,008
Tangles.

1116
01:29:11,687 --> 01:29:13,116
Johnny, go with him.

1117
01:29:20,518 --> 01:29:21,664
(TICKING)

1118
01:29:26,278 --> 01:29:29,627
MAN: Where is it? Where's
the brick? What's happening?
What did you do with it?

1119
01:29:29,702 --> 01:29:32,091
MAN 1: I didn't touch
the brick.
You better give it back.

1120
01:29:32,166 --> 01:29:33,344
(THUDDING)

1121
01:29:33,734 --> 01:29:35,010
(BANGING)

1122
01:29:36,391 --> 01:29:38,147
(ARGUING)

1123
01:29:39,271 --> 01:29:41,245
(THUDDING)

1124
01:29:52,230 --> 01:29:53,507
(GUN FIRING)

1125
01:30:15,686 --> 01:30:17,093
PIN: What's happening?

1126
01:30:17,158 --> 01:30:18,435
Cops?
TANGLES: No.

1127
01:30:19,174 --> 01:30:20,516
The brick...

1128
01:30:21,702 --> 01:30:23,295
The brick is gone.

1129
01:30:24,999 --> 01:30:27,682
Make peace, huh? Talk it out?

1130
01:30:28,358 --> 01:30:30,627
Get your boys in my den
so's you could snag it
under my nose!

1131
01:30:30,694 --> 01:30:32,799
No, it's not that!
Was it bad, Tug?

1132
01:30:32,902 --> 01:30:35,585
Snag it so I don't know,
or sell it off to flat
the war odds!

1133
01:30:35,654 --> 01:30:37,956
You're right!
I really did all that!
Pin, think about it!

1134
01:30:39,686 --> 01:30:40,897
Tug, no!

1135
01:30:41,350 --> 01:30:42,627
(GRUNTING)

1136
01:30:51,718 --> 01:30:52,667
PIN: Brendan!

1137
01:30:53,702 --> 01:30:54,650
No!

1138
01:30:57,895 --> 01:30:58,909
Help me!

1139
01:31:02,022 --> 01:31:04,411
(GROANING)
No! No!

1140
01:31:05,606 --> 01:31:07,494
Brendan! Please!

1141
01:31:21,798 --> 01:31:23,205
Please help me.

1142
01:31:24,838 --> 01:31:26,299
MAN: It's the cops!

1143
01:31:27,014 --> 01:31:28,541
Cops!
Help me.

1144
01:31:30,278 --> 01:31:31,685
Brendan, please.

1145
01:31:45,670 --> 01:31:47,263
(PANTING)

1146
01:31:47,750 --> 01:31:49,474
(POLICE SIRENS WAILING)

1147
01:32:05,510 --> 01:32:07,746
BRENDAN: Hey, where are you?
BRAIN: Library. Where are you?

1148
01:32:07,814 --> 01:32:09,341
Did she blow last night?

1149
01:32:09,414 --> 01:32:12,000
No, stayed there until 6:30,
then walked to school.

1150
01:32:12,070 --> 01:32:14,688
You didn't give her a ride,
did you?
No.

1151
01:32:15,174 --> 01:32:17,116
She came to school,
straight from Tug's?
Yeah.

1152
01:32:17,190 --> 01:32:18,717
She there now?
Yeah.

1153
01:32:18,886 --> 01:32:20,315
Not with me, but here.

1154
01:32:20,390 --> 01:32:23,260
All right, tell her
I wanna meet up on the field
in half an hour.

1155
01:32:23,334 --> 01:32:25,571
Then go home, get some sleep.

1156
01:32:25,862 --> 01:32:27,039
Will do.

1157
01:33:14,246 --> 01:33:15,937
Did you see it all?

1158
01:33:16,646 --> 01:33:18,369
With The Pin and Tug?

1159
01:33:20,934 --> 01:33:23,073
No, I took your advice
and didn't go.

1160
01:33:25,542 --> 01:33:26,524
No?

1161
01:33:28,294 --> 01:33:29,756
What happened?

1162
01:33:30,982 --> 01:33:32,837
The papers say six dead,

1163
01:33:33,478 --> 01:33:35,071
three around the house,

1164
01:33:35,589 --> 01:33:38,524
girl in the back of Tug's car,
and The Pin and Tug.

1165
01:33:39,718 --> 01:33:40,667
Yeah?

1166
01:33:42,118 --> 01:33:45,500
Tug tried to shoot his way out
when the police got there.

1167
01:33:45,574 --> 01:33:48,291
They tied him to Dode, too.
Same gun.

1168
01:33:48,646 --> 01:33:49,890
And the girl.

1169
01:33:51,398 --> 01:33:52,347
Huh.

1170
01:33:55,238 --> 01:33:58,467
Well, it's a good thing
you werert there.
Yeah.

1171
01:34:01,766 --> 01:34:04,002
Do you think
the girl was Emily?

1172
01:34:06,982 --> 01:34:08,226
Probably.

1173
01:34:12,902 --> 01:34:14,331
You loved her.

1174
01:34:16,710 --> 01:34:18,052
Yeah, I did.

1175
01:34:19,078 --> 01:34:21,762
You did all of this
because you loved her.

1176
01:34:22,598 --> 01:34:24,354
And now it's finished.

1177
01:34:25,766 --> 01:34:26,714
No.

1178
01:34:29,862 --> 01:34:30,909
What?

1179
01:34:31,621 --> 01:34:33,247
It's not finished.

1180
01:34:34,470 --> 01:34:37,187
Tug pulled the trigger on Em,
and he got the fall for it.

1181
01:34:37,254 --> 01:34:40,156
But the bulls could have
found that out without me.

1182
01:34:40,230 --> 01:34:44,124
I set out to know who put her
in the spot, who put her
in front of the gun.

1183
01:34:45,702 --> 01:34:47,393
That was you, angel.

1184
01:34:49,062 --> 01:34:51,069
What are you talking about?

1185
01:34:52,518 --> 01:34:53,827
It was you.

1186
01:34:57,990 --> 01:34:59,484
Brendan.
What?

1187
01:35:01,542 --> 01:35:04,476
You want the whole tale?
You want me to tell it to you?

1188
01:35:05,094 --> 01:35:06,555
Tell it to me.

1189
01:35:10,277 --> 01:35:12,579
All right, from the top.

1190
01:35:15,142 --> 01:35:17,825
You had your fingers
in Brad Bramish
for appearances

1191
01:35:17,894 --> 01:35:21,123
and to keep him buying
from The Pin,
who you were hooked with.

1192
01:35:21,189 --> 01:35:24,353
When Emily came
to you and Brad,
you saw her for what she was,

1193
01:35:24,421 --> 01:35:26,788
an insecure little girl
trying to get in.

1194
01:35:27,686 --> 01:35:29,726
She goes on the back burner.

1195
01:35:30,822 --> 01:35:33,757
Meanwhile,
maybe you're getting bored,
or maybe just greedy,

1196
01:35:33,830 --> 01:35:36,218
but when The Pin scores big
with the bricks,
you take your shot.

1197
01:35:36,294 --> 01:35:39,906
You hook one, take half,
cut it back to size,
but you cut it back bad.

1198
01:35:40,006 --> 01:35:43,519
Maybe accidentally,
maybe to down The Pin's
operation, doesn't matter.

1199
01:35:43,590 --> 01:35:47,681
You put it back.
Poor Frisco doses off it
and lands in a coma.

1200
01:35:48,550 --> 01:35:51,070
So now The Pin's fuming,
maybe he's jealous of Brad,

1201
01:35:51,142 --> 01:35:53,924
so he comes to Brad's car
looking for blood,
or at least a scape.

1202
01:35:53,990 --> 01:35:57,306
You're in big trouble.
There's gonna be a war
over this.

1203
01:35:57,990 --> 01:36:01,852
And there's Emily.
She trusts you.
She wants in.

1204
01:36:03,174 --> 01:36:04,451
It's duck soup.
No!

1205
01:36:04,518 --> 01:36:06,754
You frame her
for the bad brick,
then you cut her loose.

1206
01:36:06,821 --> 01:36:08,676
You turn on your heel
and bite her in the throat.

1207
01:36:08,741 --> 01:36:10,847
Last week at the payphone,
Del Rio and Sarmentoso,

1208
01:36:10,918 --> 01:36:12,576
she saw something
she was scared of.

1209
01:36:12,646 --> 01:36:14,882
Tug's car driving by,
The Pin riding shotgun.

1210
01:36:14,949 --> 01:36:16,411
But she wouldn't have seen
The Pin.

1211
01:36:16,486 --> 01:36:20,479
No, she was across the street,
angel. She saw the
driver's side. She saw you.

1212
01:36:21,446 --> 01:36:24,261
She saw you, and she ran
like she saw some devil.

1213
01:36:24,518 --> 01:36:25,598
Brendan, why...

1214
01:36:25,669 --> 01:36:28,222
She took the hit,
Dode hid her away,
but The Pin was on to her.

1215
01:36:28,293 --> 01:36:30,660
He tracked her down
and told her to meet,
that they'd make good.

1216
01:36:30,726 --> 01:36:33,660
He gave her a time and a place
and sent Tug.
Just to get the straight.

1217
01:36:33,734 --> 01:36:36,800
But maybe you had
talked Tug up.
Or maybe he just blew a fuse.

1218
01:36:36,870 --> 01:36:38,812
But when Em sprung it on him
that she had her kid,

1219
01:36:38,886 --> 01:36:41,569
he did what anyone could
count on Tug doing.

1220
01:36:41,894 --> 01:36:43,203
He hit her.

1221
01:36:43,366 --> 01:36:46,432
She took the hit for you,
and you let her take it.

1222
01:36:46,502 --> 01:36:47,647
Stop! Stop!
That's the tale.

1223
01:36:47,718 --> 01:36:50,620
Are you gonna tell me
it's not?
Stop it. It's not.

1224
01:36:56,934 --> 01:36:58,876
Will you tell me it's not?

1225
01:36:59,078 --> 01:37:00,223
It's not.

1226
01:37:05,446 --> 01:37:06,875
It isn't true.

1227
01:37:09,766 --> 01:37:11,293
I hope it isn't.

1228
01:37:13,286 --> 01:37:16,101
I want you to have been
on my side all along,

1229
01:37:17,286 --> 01:37:19,774
not just trying
to get me under your thumb,

1230
01:37:20,166 --> 01:37:22,948
like Brad and The Pin and Tug.

1231
01:37:24,485 --> 01:37:26,428
But I think you knew
that party was gonna blow up.

1232
01:37:26,501 --> 01:37:28,509
I think that was
your final play.

1233
01:37:30,214 --> 01:37:31,937
But I hope I'm wrong.

1234
01:37:34,181 --> 01:37:36,286
I hope everything
I wrote in the note

1235
01:37:36,357 --> 01:37:39,805
that I dropped
at Gary Truemars office
this morning is wrong.

1236
01:37:40,454 --> 01:37:43,749
About your and Brad's
involvement
in The Pin's runnings.

1237
01:37:45,670 --> 01:37:49,826
And I hope you didn't steal
the brick last night
in your purse.

1238
01:37:51,430 --> 01:37:52,674
I didn't.

1239
01:37:53,733 --> 01:37:54,781
Good.

1240
01:37:56,134 --> 01:37:59,614
That means you didn't
let me walk into
a slaughterhouse.

1241
01:38:00,166 --> 01:38:03,843
And you didn't lead
The Pin and Tug and
their crews to the slaughter.

1242
01:38:04,997 --> 01:38:09,056
And when Trueman
reads my note, takes my cue
and searches your locker,

1243
01:38:10,501 --> 01:38:12,508
he won't find a damn thing.

1244
01:38:26,725 --> 01:38:27,903
Brendan,

1245
01:38:29,446 --> 01:38:30,875
don't do this.

1246
01:38:37,093 --> 01:38:38,370
It's done.

1247
01:38:39,782 --> 01:38:40,829
Done?

1248
01:38:47,526 --> 01:38:49,413
Well, that's most of it.

1249
01:38:50,566 --> 01:38:52,060
Nine out of 10.

1250
01:38:54,182 --> 01:38:56,702
I told Em to tell Tugger
it was his.

1251
01:38:58,149 --> 01:39:00,320
Told her it would
soften him up.

1252
01:39:03,461 --> 01:39:07,106
She said she wished she could
keep it, but she didn't
love the father.

1253
01:39:09,125 --> 01:39:12,159
I was gonna drive her down
to the doctor the next day.

1254
01:39:12,678 --> 01:39:14,139
Most wouldn't.

1255
01:39:15,046 --> 01:39:17,347
She was already
starting to show.

1256
01:39:18,821 --> 01:39:20,228
Three months.

1257
01:39:22,534 --> 01:39:24,705
Do you know whose kid
that makes it?

1258
01:39:26,566 --> 01:39:28,605
Or have you known all along?

1259
01:39:32,134 --> 01:39:34,338
Mother...

1260
01:39:53,733 --> 01:39:55,904
You get your straight?
Yeah.

1261
01:39:55,974 --> 01:39:58,340
I wouldn't have, if I...
It's all right.

1262
01:40:00,326 --> 01:40:04,003
Chuck Burns came to.
The knife guy. He spilled
it all to the bulls.

1263
01:40:04,197 --> 01:40:07,972
Turns out Brad Bramish
hired him on his own.
It was just a grudge thing.

1264
01:40:08,485 --> 01:40:09,532
Fits.

1265
01:40:11,206 --> 01:40:13,573
You did good, Brain. Go sleep.

1266
01:40:14,630 --> 01:40:16,059
Yeah. You, too.

1267
01:40:23,686 --> 01:40:25,475
What'd she whisper to you?

1268
01:40:30,150 --> 01:40:32,157
She called me a dirty word.

1269
01:40:34,246 --> 01:40:36,734
All right,
you don't have to tell me.
